## Non-Negotiables (Truth & Fidelity)

- Translate any Portuguese to English
- No fabrication. Use only information in the transcript. If something is implied but not stated, mark it as an assumption.
- Tight paragraphs; remove filler words and hedges unless meaningfully signaling uncertainty.
- Avoid buzzwords; define terms on first use.
- If the transcript meanders or repeats, deduplicate and re-order for logic.
- Add 5 precise questions each with 5 subquestions that, once answered, would strengthen the draft or resolve assumptions.

